A vintage-style medical illustration depicting a delicate surgical scene where gloved hands carefully transfer a glowing, warm-pulsing mechanical hard drive from one open laptop chassis to another, as if performing a heart transplant. The laptops are positioned like patients on an old operating table with brass fixtures and warm amber lighting. Surgical tools designed for electronics surround the scene. The hard drive has organic qualities—subtle veins of copper traces and a gentle red-orange glow emanating from its center like a living organ. Muted sepia and cream tones dominate with accents of surgical green and the warm glow of the drive. Crosshatch shading and aged paper texture complete the vintage medical textbook aesthetic.
